cards.praxis: A walled-in city with labyrinthine streets and few inhabitants.
Mysterious shapeshifters from beneath the city.
Deadly storms with excessive lightning and boiling rain
A string of thefts across the city. The people are slow to trust.
Dawnwalkers, a ritualistic human cult, and the Secret Police, a shadow government of the shapeshifter creatures
Their blood is considered an addictive delicacy
<@!352987772983967745> 3 of Clubs Praxis Find a safe place to hide.
A rare metal worth a great deal. Resistant to the dangerous storms
The head of council Shenil, a charismatic beast folk with the rare power to enter sunlight unharmed
A black skeleton key, with sharpened edges. It was originally the key to their prison, they had witnessed it in use frequently by their captors.
Pain. They lived in a life of hellish torment beforehand, with bloodletting almost every day that left them weak and tired. If they are captured again...Their fate could be rather painful.

Raised above the belowgrounds from the depths of the Dawnwalkers' den. They were used essentially as livestock for their blood and trapped for a majority of their childhood, but had escaped just as those strings of thefts began.

As a member of the beastfolk, there is danger in existing. The sun burns and saps the strength of them, leaving them useless and easily returned to captivity. They utilize their unique shapeshifting abilities to avoid the suspicion of members of the Dawnwalkers.
an umbrella with an extremely sharpened end. It serves as both a shield from the sun and a weapon in an emergency. They learned to use it after one foolish childhood escapade out of the underground
they want to be free, without fear or restraint. They will have to say goodbye to their family if they go through with it

from below the city, they want to leave because they fear both sides of the conflict. They are half human and half beast. They are unable to shapeshift and instead take on one form with features from both sides of their family. They are still allergic to sunlight and while slightly less intoxicating than one of the beast folk it is still just as good making them an easy target to spot if they leave the underground.
wielding the weird puts them in immediate danger without any benefits for blending in. It more so puts them at a disadvantage but they do have heightened senses

cards.praxis: The Midnight Steel, a rival scavenger group
The perpetual motion engine is a LIE!!
Dr. Kassandra Wheeler, the leader of the Mechanists
An ancestral brass coin. Family heirloom used to make decisions.
It is what my father did, and what their parents did before them. I am an anchor to the city's prosperity.
Grew up in The Underline District. Middle class family.
I can sense creatures affected by the blight, and can tell how far their minds are lost to it
Lost her brother to the Blight
Left the Mekanists to study the Blight
Space is scary, back up your brain now!
Debate/conflict over the use of Voidlane tech/abilities.
The Angels, curators of the Library of Souls
The Unfulfilled, residents of pirate libraries trying to take advantage of the SNDRAs
The Angels know the voidlanes are failing
The Melogs, a hive mind of empathic creatures.
Discover the cause of the voidlane pulses
Harlem is seeking control of the SNDRAs
Learned parkour by climbing the shelves of the library.
As a former SNDRA, I don't want others to go through that.
Former Angel of a local Library, fed up with mundanity.
You Haven't Seen Enough Hentai To Know Where This Is Going
People Can Be Spaceships Too! (aka. Voidlanes Are Stealing My Job).
Failure to comply will result in complete stack erasure. You have been warned.
An old soul brought out from The Cloud, to pay back an old debt.
Thought-stealing and intent-reading; exposure to dreams, nightmares, and secrets that should be left unknown.
Her colony was wiped out by a plague, she wants to prevent that from happening to anyone else.
She grew up on a very traditional colony on a moon of Jupiter which was wiped out by a plague.
Distrusts the Voidlanes as a possible cause of THE PLAGUE that wiped out her colony Considers it very dangerous and addictive.
tracking hunting survival, being stuck on a foreign planets for years
being the best survivalist in the universe, the title (self titled) of best survivalist in the universe
Nimbus Station on the outer rim, exploring new planets
being one with the planet, lose track of my main goal and just looking to survival
tech for quickly collecting and distilling snow from mountain peaks for water, heat from fires used as form of fuel, tools that come off of balloons, different baskets have different tools

familiars need to be given care and be constantly connected with, if they are pushed too hard the familiar may snap and turn on the person or they could be completely controlled - also the kind of familiar you have impacts how others view you - also one can only have a familiar if someone who truly loves them dies or decides to pass on their familiar to them
fire planet with hot air balloons as transportation and residential spaces
everyone has a familiar (kind of like a guardian angel) that can do a certain kind of magic and the familiars do what they think the person would want (although it doesn't always work out)

flares from the planet's surface, adaptation is flare shielding (but it's expensive and difficult to install, need access to certain kinds of familiars) - also some small level of prediction technology for when and where flares occur

higher class families (and their familiars) are working to abolish pilgrimages to keep the power insular, usage of familiars is becoming more aggressive and usage of lower class familiars is being threatened - heavy division between classes and "ranks" of families and familiars that is enforced strictly
Important faction = the upper class of familiar-holders, rival factions are upper classes from other places and also everyone else kinda hates them

familiars have autonomy, so they can leave or turn on you as they wish - people with no familiars or no family are the most vulnerable, or those who have familiars who have been pushed in their past. people need to get really close to their familiars and grow and develop with them, or else the familiars may not do as you wish or choose to leave. creating new familiars from animals is a big undertaking with a lot of risk of failure, and requires a pilgrimage to the fire surface from the snow-peaked mountains.
the upper echelon opposes the goal, their agenda is complete and utter tyrannical/oligarchical power (through nepotism)

some people have started communities in other places, no one knows if they actually exist - the only means of learning this secret is to go explore and get lucky, or hear rumors that lead you to communities
most valuable good is food, the risk taken is either going into caves to collect the more nutritious version of it or grow it on one's balloon and be constantly a bit hungry
elders, there are only a few who survive to old age and they earn respect by surviving long enough
dismantling the classist regime of the world in one way or another. success is measured through empowering the party and the people
Archipelago can be used, based on meteorological events, though the mechanism that operates it isn't known.
Ink is a limited resource that the body naturally produces. You can both overproduce and overuse the ink, causing drastic bodily dysfunction.
The Crossroads, Old ruins that are being exploited, technologically regressive time period
Every cephalopod has an internal chem kit that allows them to produce ink they can control the properties of (8 limbs of Octopi magic)
It's a metaphor for global warming
Trade conflict based on the control of the Calamari over The Crossroads. They use the control to exploit different species of valuable substances to their Inkmetry
Milked Dry Revolutionaries. Kraken pirate army. Inkchemist mafia controlling the Crossroads.
Old and Young are particularly vulnerable. InkChemists use substances to create different effects and some cause substance abuse issues, along with other negative bodily effects.
Someone or something knows the full secrets of The Crossroads. If you can find/communicate with the hidden force, you could maybe gain control.
Some kind of secret spice that an Avian person can take to sense the weather. Delicate political situation with the Avians and the physical risk of not being in the water.
Jibbers Crabst an ancient crustacean that talks very slowly and has lived for thousands of years.
Re-establish the organisation of Science!™ Forge a political alliance to get funding.
<@!378989057243480068> A of Hearts Praxis spray ink at ground
Octant. Basically a sextant but for octopi
My pop was a merchant. Always dreamed of finding ivory pearls in the deep ocean, but he never reached his goal. Now that he's gone, I'm taking up his mantle
Young merchant in the urban centre of Tentacolo. Left the city in search of riches aboard the Santa Polpo Frigate
on the lower end of the merchant class, I have to be crafty when I use by basic ink sacks. No fancy explosive ink on this prawn
a wink and a smile.  Trial and error but mostly error
Guitar player from Crablabria.  Substance abuse
I make back up dancers out of ink.  Its exhausting making copies of yourself
A well trained sea turtle, Bosch, he uses for transportation. Bosch has kept him safe in his long journey to the crossroads.
Captured by the idea of science, a true believer. Wants to share, learn, and thinks the crossroads can make everyone 'rich' if shared.
Small shrimp ranch, outside of Sareno. Left to explore their world and better understand it.

A source of expression, and joy. Would sneak away from the the ranch to practice and explore his art. A talented but crudely trained inkmest. Makes lots of dangerous mistakes due to his lack of training.
a "boombox", which generates a blast of sound - disorients those in its radius
Science!™ - poor profits, low grant funding for challenging commercial interests
The University of Zilama, principle investigator in physics. Called by the science/exploration organization to support research effort
Allows me to quickly generate equipment and reagents for experiments. Easy to make mistakes on components, sometimes with disastrous results
